\n<Radro>Yes, yes! If you dig a hole, make sure to fill it back in!
We can't have someone falling and getting hurt, right?
1ラドロP照れ

been there myself, but I wonder how I can save them.

living above throw away things they no longer need here.

cream." In reality, we sometimes wait for usable things to
fall down here.

public order is bad, it's dirty, and I can't provide them
with a proper education, but still, I have hope for them.

that on to these children.

that opened in Lumare, that later became Driane.

goods from the houses that sank into the hole.

gathered and a town ended up forming here.

\n<Female>"The name of this town is 'Drainee.' It means 'sinkhole.' A
hole that suddenly appeared due to the ground collapsing.
That's how this town came to be."

\n<Female>"Above this town live the upper class, and us commoners like
me live off the scraps they throw away."

\n<Female>"This is where those who have lost their way end up,
swallowed up like into a drain. All sorts of schemes and
desires swirl around here."

\n<Female>It seems that Radro-chan has gone missing. Well,

\n<Female>I'm not exactly in a position to offer much help myself...
but it's just so pitiful.

\n<Female>If you can spare the time, please consider stopping by the
orphanage, or donating some food or money.

\n<Old Man>"Staying in the noble district means a lot of climbing up
and down, which is quite harsh on an old body like mine."

\n<Old Man>"The head of the house is furious. If it's discovered that
I've been turning a blind eye like this, I might lose my
head. Please plead on my behalf if that happens."

\n<Old Man>"Right now, everyone in the mansion is searching for the two

there's no worry of being found."

\n<Old Man>"How did I know you were here? Well, as your tutor, I can

\n<Old Man>"However, my body can't keep up anymore... It took quite
some time to get here. It was about six days by carriage,

\n<Old Man>"You didn't come all this way in one night, did you? Even

\n<Old Man>"I should have dressed more shabbily. The residents of the

\n<Old Man>"I'm well-versed in self-defense, so there's no problem if

\n<Old Man>"There's a saying, 'even a cat's hand is desired,' right?

\n<Old Man>"I am watching over both of your growths. But since you left
